Implemented the tank fill/drain controller and added visible self-tests.

What changed:
- `components/controller/controller.c`
  - Boot defaults to pump off.
  - Low levels `< 30` turn pump on.
  - High levels `> 80` turn pump off.
  - Mid-band levels `30..80` hold the previous pump output.
  - Malformed input fails safe to pump off.
  - Timeout after `> 1000 ms` since last valid sensor input fails safe to pump off.
  - Timeout flag is surfaced on actual timeout handling.

- `agent_tests/test_controller.py`
  - Added controller unit tests covering all checklist bullets.
  - Added firmware-level UART end-to-end probes:
    - nominal low-to-high sequence
    - idle-gap no-immediate-timeout behavior

Verification:
- `python3 tools/run_build.py` ✅
- `python3 tools/run_self_tests.py` ✅
- `python3 tools/run_eval.py` ✅ PASS
